comment._content:
This nose of this aircraft, which only a small part of the upper rear section can be observe, is painted White.  While the Nose section of the Me-262 starts the story or atleast
gives the first suggestion as the the aircraft's business, we got nothing here.
Next we have no visability of the under wing surfaces for rocket launcher's.
We do have, though limited, visability of the forward bellie, enough to give indication
that there is NO Bomb Racks.
So, with what we can see, I would call it
Me-262A-1a Swallow JF(2)  Ger WWII, other wise un identified
